public class RawObject

Implementation of RiakObject which interprets objects retrieved from Riak's Raw interface.

setValueStream

public void setValueStream(java.io.InputStream in,
                           java.lang.Long len)
Set the object's value as a stream. A value set here is independent of and has precedent over values set using setValue(). Calling getValue() will always return values set via setValue(), and calling getValueStream() will always return the stream set via setValueStream.

Parameters:
in - Input stream representing the object's value
len - Length of the InputStream or null if unknown. If null, the value will be buffered in memory to determine its size before sending to the server.
